@startuml
title ShopSmart — Deployment diagram (production topology & horizontal scaling)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam roundcorner 6

note as NLegend
  **Production URLs**
  • Frontend: **https://shopsmart.taj.works/**
  • REST API: **https://shopsmart-server.taj.works/**
  • Swagger UI: **https://shopsmart-swagger.taj.works/api-docs**

  **Runtime integration**
  • Auth: JWT in **localStorage**; API expects **Authorization: Bearer**
  • **CORS**: API **FRONTEND_URL** = frontend origin (no cookie-based cross-origin session)
  • Browser calls **NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL** directly (no required Next.js BFF proxy)

  **Scaling**
  • Stateless Next.js tier and stateless Express tier scale independently
  • PostgreSQL and object storage are managed services behind the API
end note

actor "End user" as User

node "Client device" {
  [Browser\nNext.js + React + Axios] as SPA
}

cloud "Frontend origin\nshopsmart.taj.works" {
  [Next.js 1\nApp Router] as Next1
  [Next.js N] as NextN
}

cloud "API origin\nshopsmart-server.taj.works" {
  [Express + Prisma\n/api] as Api1
  [Express + Prisma\n(instance N)] as ApiN
  [Swagger UI\n/api-docs] as SwaggerApi
}

cloud "Docs origin (optional)\nshopsmart-swagger.taj.works" {
  [Swagger UI\n(/api-docs)] as SwaggerDoc
}

database "PostgreSQL\n(managed)" as DB
storage "Object storage\n(S3 / R2 / …)" as Blob

User --> SPA : Use app
SPA --> Next1 : **HTTPS** pages & assets
SPA --> NextN : **HTTPS**

SPA --> Api1 : **HTTPS** JSON **REST**\n**Bearer** + **CORS**
SPA --> ApiN : **HTTPS**

SPA ..> SwaggerDoc : **HTTPS** optional\n(API documentation)
SPA ..> SwaggerApi : **HTTPS** optional\nsame host as API

SwaggerDoc ..> Api1 : **Try it out**\n→ OpenAPI server URL\n(typically API origin)

Api1 --> DB : Prisma **TCP/TLS**
ApiN --> DB : Prisma **TCP/TLS**
Api1 ..> Blob : Media **URLs**\n(optional)

note bottom of Next1
  **Horizontal scaling:** more Next.js workers or edge
  replicas; static assets may sit behind a CDN.
end note

note bottom of Api1
  **Horizontal scaling:** multiple Node/serverless
  instances. Serverless bundles must include
  **swagger-ui-dist** so /api-docs assets are not
  served as HTML (Vercel: **includeFiles**).
end note

note bottom of SwaggerDoc
  Often the **same Express** stack on a second hostname,
  or a **reverse proxy** to the API. Not a separate
  business tier unless you deploy docs-only.
end note

note bottom of DB
  **RDS / Neon / Supabase / etc.** Optional read
  replicas for read-heavy workloads.
end note

@enduml
